                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5441.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at C. P. Diaz</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Ciudad
                                Porfirio Diaz.</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <lb/> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-08">undated</date>] (Received
                        November 8, 1912—6.10 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>About 1,000 rebels in the southern part of this district, in bands of 50 or less.
                    Impossible to say who leads them. In the northern part, about 1,000 have
                    operated during the past month, but are supposed to have crossed into
                    Chihuahua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Luther T. Ellsworth.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
